In {{ill|1217|ja|1217th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1217|qq=}} ({{ill|Kenpō|ja|建保|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenpō|qq=}} 5), {{ill|Kajiwara Kagemasa|ja|梶原景実|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kajiwara Kagemasa|qq=}} (Sengōbō Ryōzen), who was the temporary {{ill|Bettō|ja|別当|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bettō|qq=}} of {{ill|Tsurugaoka Hachimangū|ja|鶴岡八幡宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsurugaoka Hachimangū|qq=}}, witnessed the passing of {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yoritomo|qq=}}, the subsequent decline of the Kajiwara family, and the fall of other notable clans such as the {{ill|Wada clan|ja|和田氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wada clan|qq=}} and {{ill|Hatakeyama clan|ja|畠山氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hatakeyama clan|qq=}}. Saddened by these events, he left Kamakura and journeyed northward, aiming for the {{ill|Ezo|ja|蝦夷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ezo|qq=}} and {{ill|Kuril Islands|ja|千島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuril Islands|qq=}}.
Eventually, Kagemasa settled in Takai-shi-hama (currently in Karakuwa, Kesennuma City), a region associated with {{ill|Fujiwara Takahira|ja|藤原高衡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara Takahira|qq=}} (Motoyoshi Shiro Takahira). There, he constructed a shrine beside his residence to house images of Yoritomo, Kagetoki, and Kagesue, praying for the repose of their spirits and establishing Kajiwara Shrine. Sengōbō was a spiritual mentor to Minamoto no Yoritomo. Later, he also founded {{ill|Hayama Shrine|ja|早馬神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hayama Shrine|qq=}}, and the hereditary position of {{ill|guji|ja|宮司|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/guji|qq=}} (chief priest) was maintained by the direct descendants of the Kajiwara family.
== Access ==
The shrine is a 5-minute walk from the Takai-shi-hama bus stop, accessible via JR {{ill|Yahata Bridge Station|ja|八幡大橋駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yahata Bridge Station|qq=}}.
